brains.com/kotlin/2026/05/kotlin-ecosystem-mentorship-program/)
The Kotlin Ecosystem Mentorship Program pilot concludes with four successf=
ul open-source collaborations and plans for future cohorts.
blog.jetbrains.com (https://blog.jetbrains.com/kotlin/2026/05/kotlin-ecosy=
stem-mentorship-program/)

Articles
Is Kotlin Multiplatform actually worth using in 2026? (https://www.reddit.=
com/r/androiddev/comments/1sx6qkg/is_kotlin_multiplatform_kmm_actually_wor=
th_using/)
Reddit thread discussing whether it makes sense to keep using KMM in 2026=
=2C amidst the AI era.
www.reddit.com (https://www.reddit.com/r/androiddev/comments/1sx6qkg/is_ko=
tlin_multiplatform_kmm_actually_worth_using/?utm_source=3Dshare&utm_medium=
=3Dweb3x&utm_name=3Dweb3xcss&utm_term=3D1&utm_content=3Dshare_button)

Managing Gradle Daemons while Coding with AI (https://proandroiddev.com/ma=
naging-gradle-daemons-while-coding-with-ai-359cf1a4aeb3)
This article discusses how to use a PreToolUse hook to automatically prune=
 stale Java processes and reclaim your RAM.
proandroiddev.com (https://proandroiddev.com/managing-gradle-daemons-while=
-coding-with-ai-359cf1a4aeb3)

Threads=2C Mutexes=2C Semaphores=2C Dispatchers & Parallelism: The Mental=
 Model Most Engineers Are Still Missing (https://medium.com/@mr.califer/th=
reads-mutexes-semaphores-dispatchers-parallelism-the-mental-model-most-eng=
ineers-are-still-e8df4f2438d8)
A deep dive into the 'physics' of concurrency=2C exploring how CPU behavio=
r=2C memory visibility=2C and cache-line contention shape the performance=
 of Kotlin and JVM systems.
medium.com (https://medium.com/@mr.califer/threads-mutexes-semaphores-disp=
atchers-parallelism-the-mental-model-most-engineers-are-still-e8df4f2438d8=
)

Arrow: Error handling without flatMap (https://ivan.canet.dev/blog/2026/05=
/04/errors-without-flatmap.html)
Arrow leverages Kotlin 2.4.0 context parameters and the Raise DSL to provi=
de functional error handling that eliminates 'flatMap hell'=2C allowing de=
velopers to write concise=2C short-circuiting code that remains as readabl=
e as standard imperative logic.
ivan.canet.dev (https://ivan.canet.dev/blog/2026/05/04/errors-without-flat=
map.html)

Sponsored
View the latest HubSpot Developer Platform updates in Spring Spotlight (ht=
tps://www.vpdae.com/redirect/xud34l74vwiv3j0dhuoe69kndxl)
Spring Spotlight 2026 is live and we=E2=80=99ve rounded up the top updates=
 for you. See what's new for the HubSpot Developer Platform! Ship faster w=
ith AI coding tools like Cursor=2C Claude Code=2C and Codex. Build MCP-pow=
ered AI connectors=2C run serverless functions with support for UI extensi=
ons=2C and use date-based versioning to streamline roadmap planning.
www.vpdae.com (https://www.vpdae.com/redirect/xud34l74vwiv3j0dhuoe69kndxl)

Android
Ultimate Android SDE2/SDE3 Interview Roadmap (2026) (https://medium.com/@v=
ikasacsoni9211/ultimate-android-sde2-sde3-interview-roadmap-2026-4e6af7cf1=
fa1)
An SDE2/SDE3 roadmap for 2026 focusing on architectural tradeoffs=2C Jetpa=
ck Compose internals=2C and production-scale debugging over basic framewor=
k memorization.
medium.com (https://medium.com/@vikasacsoni9211/ultimate-android-sde2-sde3=
-interview-roadmap-2026-4e6af7cf1fa1)

From 5 fps to 30 fps: What the TFLite Defaults Are Hiding (https://proandr=
oiddev.com/from-5-fps-to-30-fps-what-the-tflite-defaults-are-hiding-a8fbf0=
d20ff6)
A guide to optimizing on-device machine learning by auditing TFLite defaul=
ts=2C implementing explicit delegate cascades=2C enabling OpenCL kernel pe=
rsistence=2C and pinning worker threads to high-performance cores.
proandroiddev.com (https://proandroiddev.com/from-5-fps-to-30-fps-what-the=
-tflite-defaults-are-hiding-a8fbf0d20ff6)

More Than the Sum of Its Parts: Rethinking Android Performance at Target (=
https://tech.target.com/blog/rethinking-android-performance)
