In this article=2C Abdulahi Osoble details a multi-layered security strate=
gy that moves beyond simple access tokens by implementing mTLS with per-de=
vice certificates and Play Integrity to verify both user identity and hard=
ware-backed device trust.
www.kadirkid.dev (https://www.kadirkid.dev/exploring-mtls/)

ZeroMQ on Android: Bridging a Linux Service with PUB SUB (https://levelup.=
gitconnected.com/zeromq-on-android-bridging-a-linux-service-with-pub-sub-4=
3ecf52209fa)
In this article=2C James Cullimore explains how to implement a high-perfor=
mance=2C low-latency messaging layer between a Linux service and an Androi=
d app using ZeroMQ's PUB/SUB pattern=2C bypassing the overhead of traditio=
nal HTTP or gRPC stacks.
levelup.gitconnected.com (https://levelup.gitconnected.com/zeromq-on-andro=
id-bridging-a-linux-service-with-pub-sub-43ecf52209fa)

Videos
How to Handle Exceptions in Kotlin Flows (https://blog.jetbrains.com/kotli=
n/2026/05/kotlin-ecosystem-mentorship-program/)
Exceptions can be thrown from within our flows=2C just like anywhere else=
 in our Kotlin code. In this video=2C Dave Leeds shows the right and wrong=
